#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>

int main() {
    std::ofstream file("data.txt");

    // Forgetting to check if file opened!
    file << "Hello" << std::endl;

    // File might not be open!
    return 0;
}

phase2.explanation:
You didn't check if the file opened successfully!

**The fix:**
```cpp
std::ofstream file("data.txt");
if (file.is_open()) {
    file << "Hello" << std::endl;
} else {
    std::cout << "Failed to open file!" << std::endl;
}
```

**PlusPlus-chan says:**
"Always check if a file opened successfully. Silent failures are the worst."

